structMember.name: estimatedRemainingBackupTime
structMember.description: Calculated estimate of remaining backup time Dependencies: The value is only defined if a battery capacity test is executed. The parameter value is undefined if a battery backup time test is executed. The parameter value is undefined if parameter testState is PENDING. Unit: 1 minute Undefined value: -1

structMember.name: measuredConsumedCapacityInTest
structMember.description: Measured total consumed capacity from test start until execution of this action Dependencies: The parameter value is undefined if parameter testState is PENDING. Unit: 1 Ah Undefined value: -1

structMember.name: measuredElapsedTime
structMember.description: Time from test start until execution of this action Dependencies: The parameter value is undefined if parameter testState is PENDING. Unit: 1 minute Undefined value: -1

structMember.name: estimatedBatteryStateOfHealth
structMember.description: Estimated state-of-health of the tested battery. State-Of-Health is calculated as: estimatedNominalBatteryCapacity / referenceBatteryCapacity * 100 Dependencies: The parameter value is undefined if a battery backup time test was executed. Unit: 1 % Undefined value: -1

structMember.name: estimatedNominalBatteryCapacity
structMember.description: Estimated nominal battery capacity of the tested battery Dependencies: The parameter value is undefined if a battery backup time test was executed. Unit: 1 Ah Undefined value: -1

structMember.name: initiation
structMember.description: Describes how the battery test was initiated.

structMember.name: measuredBackupTime
structMember.description: The measured time from test start until end of test Unit: 1 minute Undefined value: -1

structMember.name: measuredConsumedCapacity
structMember.description: Measured total consumed capacity from test start until end of test Unit: 1 Ah Undefined value: -1

structMember.name: outcome
structMember.description: Outcome of the automatic evaluation of the battery test Possible values: • UNDEFINED • PASSED • FAILED
structMember.dependencies: For a battery capacity test, the evaluation is done by comparing the estimatedBatteryStateOfHealth with the minimumStateOfHealth, if test mode is set to CONFIGURED. If testMode is set to AUTOMATIC, the estimatedBatteryStateOfHealth is compared with 70%. For a battery backup time test, the evaluation is done by comparing the measuredBackupTime with the minimumBackupTime.

structMember.name: startDate
structMember.description: The date the battery test was started. Format: "YYYYMMDD" Undefined value: "000000"

structMember.name: startTime
structMember.description: The time the battery test was started. Format: "HH:MM", 24 h format Undefined value: "--:--"

enumMember.name: UNDEFINED
enumMember.description: No automatic evaluation was done due to forced initiation. The test result needs manual evaluation.

enumMember.name: PASSED
enumMember.description: Test did not indicate underperforming batteries.

enumMember.name: FAILED
enumMember.description: Test indicated underperforming batteries and an alarm was raised.

enumMember.name: AUTOMATIC
enumMember.description: Pre-defined values are used at the periodic test.

enumMember.name: CONFIGURED
enumMember.description: User configured values are used at the periodic test.

enumMember.name: DISABLED
enumMember.description: Periodic tests are disabled.

enum.name: AvailStatus
enum.description: The availability status is used to qualify the operational state. It indicates why the operational state has changed its value.

enumMember.name: IN_TEST
enumMember.description: The resource is undergoing a test procedure. If the administrative state is locked or shutting down, normal users are prevented from using the resource.

enumMember.name: FAILED
enumMember.description: The resource has an internal fault that prevents it from operating.

enumMember.name: POWER_OFF
enumMember.description: The resource requires power to be applied and is not powered on.

enumMember.name: OFF_LINE
enumMember.description: The resource requires a routine operation to be performed. This routine operation is to place the resource online and make it available for use. The operation may be manual or automatic, or both. The operational state is disabled.

enumMember.name: OFF_DUTY
enumMember.description: The resource has been made inactive by an internal control process.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY
enumMember.description: The resource cannot operate because some other resource on which it depends is unavailable.

enumMember.name: DEGRADED
enumMember.description: The service available from the resource is degraded in some respect.

enumMember.name: NOT_INSTALLED
enumMember.description: The resource represented by the managed object is not present, or is incomplete.

enumMember.name: LOG_FULL
enumMember.description: Indicates a log full condition. The semantics are defined in CCITT Rec. X.735 | ISO/IEC 10164-6.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_LOCKED
enumMember.description: The administrative state of a resource that this resource depends on is locked. or the availability status of the other resource is dependency locked.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_FAILED
enumMember.description: The availability status of a resource that this resource depends on is failed or dependency failed.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_SHUTTINGDOWN
enumMember.description: The administrative state of a resource that this resource depends on is shutting down. or the availability status of the other resource is dependency shutting down.

enumMember.name: PENDING
enumMember.description: On demand test is pending.

enumMember.name: IN_PROGRESS
enumMember.description: Battery test is in progress.

enumMember.name: AUTOMATIC_PERIODIC
enumMember.description: Periodic test if testMode is AUTOMATIC.

enumMember.name: CONFIGURED_PERIODIC
enumMember.description: Periodic test if testMode is CONFIGURED.

enumMember.name: MAINS_FAILURE_PERIODIC
enumMember.description: Periodic test initiated from mains power failure.

enumMember.name: ON_DEMAND
enumMember.description: Initiated via action startBatteryTest and parameter forced = false.

enumMember.name: ON_DEMAND_FORCED
enumMember.description: Initiated via action startBatteryTest and parameter forced = true.

enumMember.name: DISABLED
enumMember.description: The resource is totally inoperable.

enumMember.name: ENABLED
enumMember.description: The resource is partially or fully operable.

class.name: BatteryBackup
class.description: This MO models a battery backup controlled by a BFU or BPA unit. The functionality represented by this MO is dependent on the existence of a FieldReplaceableUnit MO of type BFU or BPA. From 18.Q1 the reservedBy attribute must be empty before MO can be deleted..

action.name: readBatteryTestResult
action.description: Action for reading out the result of a finished battery test. Output data is stored persistently. This means that the result can always be read for the last finished on demand test and periodic test separately. The action is valid for battery capacity and backup time tests.

parameter.name: testType
parameter.description: Type of battery test to read result for.

action.name: readBatteryTestStatus
action.description: Action for reading out the status of an ongoing battery test (testState is IN_PROGRESS or PENDING). Valid for on demand test and periodic test. Valid for battery capacity and backup time tests. Updated values can be retrieved by issuing this action regularly during a test. Out parameter values are not stored persistently and can therefore only be read during a test. All out parameter values, except for testState, are undefined in testState PENDING.

action.name: startBatteryTest
action.description: Starts an on demand battery capacity test or battery backup time test. A battery capacity test will go into testState PENDING if the batteries are not fully charged and in parameter forced is set to False. The test will in this case be initiated when the batteries are fully charged, if this occurs within 24 h.

parameter.name: forced
parameter.description:
Specifies if forced initiation should be used or not. Forced initiation means that a number of pre-conditions are overridden and that the test can be started even if these pre-conditions are not fulfilled. Overridden pre-conditions: - batteries are considered fully charged - system is not running on batteries in case of battery time test No alarms are raised as a result of the battery test if parameter forced is set to true. Manual evaluation of the test result is needed.
Dependencies: Attribute referenceBatteryCapacity is not updated as a result of the battery test if parameter forced is set to true.

action.dependencies: A battery capacity test will be executed if attribute sharedBattery is set to False and if attribute mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect is -43 V or lower. Otherwise a backup time test will be executed.
action.disturbances: The RBS is powered from the batteries during the test. This battery discharge will make the RBS more sensitive to mains power failure during the test. Repeated battery discharge will cause aging of the batteries.

action.name: stopBatteryTest
action.description: Stops an ongoing battery capacity test or battery backup time test that was started via action startBatteryTest.

attribute.name: batteryBackupId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: batteryCurrent
attribute.description: The total measured battery backup current. When the batteries are charging, the current is positive. When the batteries are discharging, the current is negative. Undefined value: -9999 indicates no contact with battery interfacing unit such as a BFU or BPA unit.

attribute.name: batteryDisconnectTempCeaseOffset
attribute.description: The offset for the disconnect temperature below which the battery will be reconnected. Applies to both main and priority loads. The battery is reconnected when batteryTemperature < batteryDisconnectedTemp - batteryDisconnectTempCeaseOffset.

attribute.name: batteryInstallationDate
attribute.description: The date when the batteries in the battery backup of the RBS were installed and taken into service. Format: YYYYMMDD.
attribute.statusInformation: Since 18A. Replaced by installationDate in MO BatteryUnit. Planned to be removed.
attribute.dependencies: The date must not be a future date. Changing this attribute will cause the system to restart battery capacity test calculations and recalculate attribute referenceBatteryCapacity.

attribute.name: batteryTemperature
attribute.description: The current temperature reported by the battery temperature sensor installed on the battery. Undefined value represented by nil, indicates no contact with BFU, BFU has no battery or BFU has no temperature sensor.

attribute.name: batteryTestIsRunning
attribute.description:
State whether a battery test is running or not.
Possible values: - true: A battery test cycle has been started - false: Either the battery test is disabled or there is not any ongoing battery test.

attribute.name: batteryType
attribute.description: The type of battery to which the installed battery conforms. The type is related to the capabilities of the battery.
attribute.dependencies: batteryType = UNKNOWN is valid only when chargingMode = USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: batteryVoltage
attribute.description: The measured battery voltage. It is equal to the attribute systemVoltage, PowerdDistribution MO, when the battery is connected. 0 means the battery is disconnected. Undefined value represented by nil, indicates no contact with the battery interfacing unit, such as a BFU or a BPA unit.

attribute.name: boostChargeTime
attribute.description: The time in boost charge. Value zero (0) means that boost charging is disabled.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED

attribute.name: boostChargeTriggerVoltage
attribute.description: Defines the trigger voltage for boost charge. When the trigger voltage is surpassed during discharge, the consecutive charging is boost charging.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: chargeMaxCurrent
attribute.description: Maximum allowed battery current during charging. The maximum battery current is limited if the maximum current supported by the BFU is lower than this defined value.

attribute.name: chargingMode
attribute.description: The type of battery charging used. If charging is user-defined, the charging algorithm and parameters must be specified. If chargingMode = AUTOMATIC, the following attributes are not used: • floatChargeVoltage • tempCompVoltageSlope • nominalTemp • tempCompMinVoltage • tempCompMaxVoltage • elevatedChargeVoltage • boostChargeTime • boostChargeTriggerVoltage • equalizeChargeTime • equalizeChargeCyclicInterval • intermittentChargeConnectVoltage • intermittentChargeConnectTime • intermittentChargeDisconnectTime

attribute.name: chargingVoltage
attribute.description: The desired battery voltage for charging at 25 degrees Celsius.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is relevant only when attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: equalizeChargeCyclicInterval
attribute.description: The number of days between equalize charging. The cycle is reset at restart.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: equalizeChargeTime
attribute.description: The time in equalize charge. Value zero (0) means that equalize charging is disabled. To enable equalize charging, the value must be set to a number other than zero (0).
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: increasedChargeVoltage
attribute.description: The charge voltage used at boost charging and equalize charging.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: intermittentChargeConnectTime
attribute.description: Defines the period following disconnection after which the battery is reconnected. Used in intermittent charging.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: intermittentChargeConnectVoltage
attribute.description: Defines the minimum battery voltage level allowed for a disconnected battery. When minimum level is reached, the battery is reconnected. Used in intermittent charging.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: intermittentChargeDisconnectTime
attribute.description: Defines the time until the batteries are disconnected (during this time the batteries are connected). Value zero (0) means that intermittent charging is not enabled.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: minimumBackupTime
attribute.description: The minimum requirement for backup time for the installed batteries when conducting a battery backup time test. An alarm is raised if measured backup time is shorter than minimumBackupTime.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if sharedBattery is set to true.

attribute.name: minimumStateOfHealth
attribute.description: The minimum value for the State-of-Health of the battery backup system. An alarm is raised if stateOfHealth value for the battery backup system is lower than minimumStateOfHealth value.
attribute.dependencies: The attribute is only relevant if sharedBattery is set to false.

attribute.name: nextScheduledTestDate
attribute.description: Date of next scheduled periodic battery test. Format: "YYYYMMDD".
attribute.dependencies: The value is undefined if testMode has the value DISABLED.

attribute.name: nominalTemp
attribute.description: Nominal temperature for temperature compensated charging.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: referenceBatteryCapacity
attribute.description:
The initial nominal battery capacity. The value is extracted from intelligent batteries as a sum of all installed batteries’ nominal capacity. For batteries that cannot communicate, the value is calculated at the first battery capacity test. If the capacity value becomes significantly higher at a succeeding battery capacity test, the value is replaced with the highest value.
Undefined value: -1 indicates that no value has been retrieved.
attribute.dependencies: The value is either the sum of all battery units initial nominal capacity or the result of the first conducted battery capacity test of the battery system. A battery capacity test can only be executed if the attribute sharedBattery = false.

attribute.name: sharedBattery
attribute.description: Indicates if the RBS shares a battery with another RBS or other power consumer on the site. The setting of this attributes has a great impact on the system behavior.
attribute.dependencies: If sharedBattery is set to True a backup time test will be used as battery test. A battery capacity test cannot be executed if shared batteries are used.

attribute.name: tempCompMaxVoltage
attribute.description: The maximum voltage allowed for temperature compensated charging.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: tempCompMinVoltage
attribute.description: The minimum voltage allowed for temperature compensated charging.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: tempCompVoltageSlope
attribute.description: A compensation factor that expresses the amount of voltage changes caused by temperature. Used in temperature compensated charging. Higher temperature gives a lower charging voltage. Fixed battery charging is achieved by assigning this attribute the value zero. Example: The default value -96 = -0.096 V per 1 degree Celsius, gives that a 10 degree temperature increase changes the voltage from e.g. -50.000 V to -49.040 V.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: testMode
attribute.description: The mode of the battery test.
attribute.dependencies: The following attributes are only relevant if testMode is set to CONFIGURED: testStartDay, testStartTime, testStartMonths and minimumStateOfHealth.
attribute.disturbances: Depending on values of other BatteryBackup attributes, changing this attribute can start a battery test which can cause loss of traffic.

attribute.name: testStartDay
attribute.description: The day of month for periodic battery tests.
attribute.dependencies: The attribute is relevant only when testMode has the value CONFIGURED. Combination of testStartDay and testStartMonths must be a valid date.

attribute.name: testStartMonths
attribute.description: The months in which periodic battery tests are performed. A battery test is performed in the months listed in the parameter. A month may be listed only once in the parameter.
attribute.dependencies: The attribute is only relevant if attribute testMode has the value CONFIGURED.

attribute.name: testStartTime
attribute.description: The time of day to start periodic battery tests. Format: HH:MM, 24-hour format.
attribute.dependencies: The attribute is only relevant if testMode has the value CONFIGURED.

attribute.name: userLabel
attribute.description: Label for free use.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: Defines the operational state.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: extendedSoftwareControl
attribute.description: Shows if the software has extended control over battery charging, that is, the BFU has a reduced autonomous behavior.

attribute.name: batteryDisconnectTemp
attribute.description: The temperature at which the battery is disconnected. Applies to both main and priority loads. The battery is disconnected when batteryTemperature > batteryDisconnectTemp.

attribute.name: elevatedChargeVoltage
attribute.description: The charge voltage used at boost charging and equalize charging.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is only relevant if attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: floatChargeVoltage
attribute.description: The desired battery voltage for charging at 25 degrees Celsius.
attribute.dependencies: This attribute is relevant only when attribute chargingMode in MO BatteryBackup has the value USER_DEFINED.

attribute.name: batteryDisconnectHighTemp
attribute.description: The temperature at which the battery is disconnected. Applies to both main and priority loads. The battery is disconnected when batteryTemperature > batteryDisconnectHighTemp.

attribute.name: controlDomainRef
attribute.description: The cabinet or hwGroup where functions represented by this MO are deployed.

attribute.name: reservedBy
attribute.description: Contains a list of MO instances that reserve this MO instance.

attribute.name: batteryDisconnectLevel
attribute.description: The relative level of the total capacity at which batteries are disconnected and node is shut down. Undefined value: -1 indicates that no value has been set. Batteries will not be disconnected. During deprecation period, a setting of the batteryDisconnectLevel is converted and mirrored to deprecated attribute priorityLoadUndervoltageDisconnect of MO PowerDistribution. Since the valid range of priorityLoadUndervoltageDisconnect does not span the entire range of batteryDisconnectLevel, a value of batteryDisconnectLevel that is beyond the upper range of priorityLoadUndervoltageDisconnect will result in a mirrored value that is the maximum value of priorityLoadUndervoltageDisconnect. It is the value of the batteryDisconnectLevel that is used in the application.

attribute.name: capacityAlarmLevel
attribute.description: The relative level of the total capacity at which an alarm for low remaining battery backup capacity is raised. Undefined value: -1 indicates that no value has been set. Alarm will not be raised.

attribute.name: estimatedRemainingBackupTime
attribute.description: Estimated remaining backup time at current load conditions. Undefined value: -1 indicates that no value has been retrieved.
attribute.dependencies: Attribute sharedBattery must be set to false and attribute referenceBatteryCapacity must not be undefined.

attribute.name: fullyChargedCapacity
attribute.description: Current maximum capacity of the battery backup system. Undefined value: -1 indicates that no value has been retrieved.

attribute.name: mainLoadDisconnectLevel
attribute.description: The relative level of the total capacity at which the main load is disconnected. Undefined value: -1 indicates that no value has been set. Main load will not be disconnected. During deprecation period, a setting of the mainLoadDisconnectLevel is converted and mirrored to deprecated attribute mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect of MO PowerDistribution. Since the valid range of mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect does not span the entire range of mainLoadDisconnectLevel, a value of mainLoadDisconnectLevel that is beyond the upper range of mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect will result in a mirrored value that is the maximum value of mainLoadUndervoltageDisconnect. It is the value of the mainLoadDisconnectLevel that is used in the application.

attribute.name: stateOfHealth
attribute.description: State of health of the battery backup system. Undefined value: -1 indicates that no value has been retrieved.
